law.text:
As used in this subtitle, unless the context requires otherwise:
"Department" means the Department of Insurance;
"Mine subsidence" means the collapse of underground coal mines resulting in direct damage to a structure. It does not include loss caused by earthquake, landslide, water seepage, volcanic eruption, or collapse of storm, and sewer drains;
"Mine subsidence insurance fund" or "fund" means the fund established by this subtitle and administered as determined by the department;
"Policy" means a contract of insurance providing mine subsidence insurance;
"Premium" means the gross rate charged policyholders for insurance provided by this subtitle;
"Structure" means any dwelling, building, or fixture permanently affixed to realty, but does not include land, trees, plants, or crops; and
"Administrator" means the organization designated by the commissioner of the department to administer the fund.
